Fono packaging
==============

Distribution-specific packaging recipes. Each subdirectory targets one
ecosystem; pick whichever matches your distro.

| Directory            | Target                                      |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| `slackbuild/fono/`   | NimbleX / Slackware `.SlackBuild`           |
| `aur/`               | Arch Linux AUR `PKGBUILD`                   |
| `nix/`               | Nix flake (NixOS + nix-on-any-Linux/macOS)  |
| `debian/`            | `debhelper`/`dh` recipe for Debian/Ubuntu   |
| `systemd/`           | Per-user `fono.service` shared by all above |

Release artifacts (musl static binaries for `x86_64` and `aarch64`, MSVC
`.exe` for Windows, universal binary for macOS) are built by
`.github/workflows/release.yml` on every `v*` tag and attached to a
draft GitHub Release together with `SHA256SUMS` (and a minisign
signature when the `MINISIGN_KEY` secret is set).
